<Tool
  name="clawdflare"
  pip="pip install clawdflare"
  role="MCP Server"
  repo="clawdflare"
  description="Cloudflare zone auditing from your terminal. DNS, SSL, firewall rules, cache."
>
  <h2>What it does</h2>
  <p>clawdflare is an MCP server for auditing and managing Cloudflare zones. Check DNS records, SSL settings, firewall rules, and cache configuration — all through Claude Code tool calls.</p>

  <h2>Key features</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Zone listing</strong> — see all zones in your Cloudflare account</li>
    <li><strong>DNS audit</strong> — review records, find misconfigurations</li>
    <li><strong>SSL check</strong> — verify certificate status and mode</li>
    <li><strong>Firewall rules</strong> — inspect WAF and security settings</li>
    <li><strong>Cache</strong> — review and purge cache settings</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Install</h2>
  <pre><code>pip install clawdflare</code></pre>
</Tool>
